t%20direction%2C%20and%20ultimately%20those%20designers%20will%20get%20better%20results%20using%20the%20tools%20than%20the%20average%20person%20because%20%26quot%3Bthey%20understand%20how%20to%20construct%20an%20idea%2C%20even%20if%20it's%20through%20text%20prompts%2C%26quot%3B%20Still%20told%20Fortune.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20across%20various%20industries%20are%20rushing%20to%20incorporate%20AI%20into%20their%20businesses.%20For%20example%2C%20fast%20food%20chains%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-subway-chipotle-add-tech-robots-ai-to-speed-up-orders-2022-12%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMcDonald's%2C%20Wendy's%2C%20Taco%20Bell%2C%20and%20Wingstop%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20automating%20some%20customer%20service%20functions%20by%20using%20AI-powered%20voice%20bots%20to%20take%20drive-thru%20orders%20and%20over%20the%20phone.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20changes%20have%20resulted%20in%20amplified%20fears%20among%20US%20workers%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-workers-worry-tech-ai-may-replace-jobs-gallup-poll-2023-9%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAI%20taking%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20In%20a%20September%20Gallup%20poll%2C%2022%25%20of%20college-educated%20professionals%20expressed%20concerns%20about%20technology%20like%20AI%20replacing%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%2C%20however%2C%20point%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20even%20though%20AI%20is%20booming%20and%20making%20businesses%20more%20efficient%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-ai-will-not-take-jobs-create-future-work-opportunities-2023-2%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethere%20will%20always%20be%20a%20need%20for%20human%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20behind%20the%20scenes%20to%20guide%20AI%20and%20ensure%20systems%20are%20working%20properly.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article