20whose%20new%20estimate%20of%20household%20excess%20savings%20increased%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20second%20quarter%20to%20around%20%241.3%20trillion%20compared%20to%20estimates%20of%20just%20under%20%241%20trillion%20per%20the%20unrevised%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20BEA%20revisions%20reflected%20a%20shift%20in%20how%20it%20measures%20income%20from%20real%20estate%20investment%20trusts%20and%20mutual%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThis%20could%20be%20good%20news%20for%20the%20economy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20the%20revisions%2C%20though%2C%20many%20economists%20thought%20excess%20savings%20would%20run%20out%20quickly.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frbsf.org%2Four-district%2Fabout%2Fsf-fed-blog%2Fexcess-no-more-dwindling-pandemic-savings%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESan%20Francisco%20Fed%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20updated%20in%20August%20estimated%20excess%20savings%20would%20likely%20be%20depleted%20during%20the%20third%20quarter%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20revised%20data%20suggests%20Americans%20still%20have%20a%20cushion%20to%20keep%20their%20spending%20going.%20This%20may%20give%20some%20Americans%20more%20confidence%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-economic-outlook-2024-risks-signs-struggle-torsten-slok-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esoft%20landing%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20next%20few%20months.%20Some%20economists%20are%20also%20pushing%20back%20their%20timeline%20for%20when%20they%20expect%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-economy-recession-prediction-model-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecession%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20could%20be%20good%20news%20for%20an%20economy%20experiencing%20elevated%20borrowing%20costs%20for%20households%20and%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-dating-declines-all-time-low-inflation-loneliness-friendship-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C