%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20family%20and%20I%20lived%20in%20Temecula%2C%20which%20is%20between%20San%20Diego%20and%20Orange%20County.%20For%20a%20long%20time%2C%20we%20loved%20it%20there.%20We%20enjoyed%20the%20food%20and%20being%20close%20to%20the%20beach%20and%20mountains.%20But%20there%20were%20a%20lot%20of%20downsides%20to%20living%20in%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20large%20transient%20community%20and%20I%20would%20have%20to%20keep%20my%20office%20locked.%20I%20was%20on%20a%20first-name%20basis%20with%20the%20local%20police%20department%20because%20of%20incidents%20that%20happened.%20We%20really%20didn't%20want%20our%20kids%20living%20in%20that%20type%20of%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20felt%20like%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20was%20outrageous%20and%20we%20were%20always%20working.%20Despite%20that%2C%20we%20still%20didn't%20feel%20like%20we%20were%20getting%20ahead%20in%20life.%20We%20didn't%20have%20extra%20money%20for%20vacations%20and%20we%20had%20to%20live%20very%20simply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%20we%20stopped%20loving%20the%20area.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22877%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elderkin's%20California%20home.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65257b5d6561dd877e762409%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22658%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Elderkins'%20California%20home.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Danielle%20Elderkin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20sister%20lives%20in%20the%20Poconos.%20There%20are%20many%20abandoned%2C%20rundown%20cabins%20in%20the%20area.%20In%20the%20fall%20of%202018%2C%20I%20visited%20her%20and%20I%20had%20a%20lightbulb%20moment%3A%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20could%20buy%20a%20cabin%20cheaply%2C%20fix%20it%20up%2C%20sell%20it%2C%20and%20buy%20another%20one.%20We%20could%20really%20have%20a%20fresh%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20that's%20what%20we%20did.%20In%202018%2C%20we%20found%20a%20760-square-foot%2C%201960s%20cabin%20online%20and%20purchased%20it%20for%20%2465%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20we%20didn't%20even%20see%20it%20in%20person.%20In%20February%202019%2C%20we%20sold%20our%201%2C900-square-foot%20California%20home%20and%20moved%20to%20the%20Poconos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20encountered%20a%20disaster%20in%20the%20moving%20process%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20California%20home%20was%20large%2C%20so%20we%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20stuff.%20Since%20our%20Poconos%20cabin%20was%20smaller%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20almost%20everything%20%E2%80%94%20we%20really%20didn't%20care%20about%20a%20lot%20of%20our%20possessions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20a%20good%20friend%20who%20sells%20stuff%20on%20eBay.%20We%20gave%20her%20two%20U-Hauls%20full%20of%20our%20things%20and%20just%20took%20basics%20like%20dressers%2C%20beds%2C%20and%20our%20couch.%20We%20decided%20to%20take%20one%20car%20with%20us%20and%20sell%20the%20other.%20We%20really%20downsized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20hired%20a%20moving%20company%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20the%20type%20where%20they%20drop%20off%20the%20van%2C%20you%20fill%20it%20yourself%2C%20and%20then%20they%20move%20your%20belongings.%20It%20cost%20us%20around%20%248%2C000.%20On%20the%20way%20to%20Pennsylvania%2C%20our%20moving%20van%20flipped%20over.%20About%2080%25%20of%20our%20stuff%20was%20destroyed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20week%2C%20we%20had%20no%20idea%20how%20bad%20or%20minimal%20it%20was%2C%20and%20if%20we%20were%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20salvage%20our%20stuff.%20It%20was%20kind%20of%20devastating.%20The%20items%20we%20were%20most%20worried%20about%20were%20art%20and%20our%20kids'%20memories.%20Those%20were%20irreplaceable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuckily%2C%20right%20before%20we%20left%2C%20I%20called%20my%20insurance%20agent%20to%20ask%20if%20we%20were%20covered%20for%20the%20miles%20between%20California%20and%20the%20Poconos.%20He%20gave%20us%20a%20short-term%20policy%20that%20covered%20everything%2C%20it%20cost%20only%20%2415.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20our%20stuff%20arrived%20in%20the%20Poconos%2C%20we%20had%20to%20go%20through%20everything%20and%20make%20a%20list%20of%20our%20items%20and%20look%20up%20pricing.%20Nothing%20that%20really%20mattered%20to%20us%20was%20destroyed.%20It%20really%20put%20into%20perspective%20how%20much%20stuff%20we%20really%20needed%20in%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223023%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Elderkin's%20moving%20van.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65258a7b55f52b01b35b4741%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Elderkins'%20moving%20van.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Danielle%20Elderkin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20did%20deal%20with%20inconveniences.%20Our%20couch%20was%20broken%20in%20half%20and%20our%20dressers%20smashed.%20My%20husband%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20light%20construction%20equipment%20like%20saws%20that%20were%20damaged.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20basically%20got%20the%20purchase%20price%20for%20everything%20that%20was%20destroyed.%20I%20think%20it%20was%20like%20%2415%2C000.%20We%20were%20lucky%2C%20the%20moving%20company%20was%20only%20going%20to%20pay%20us%2010%20cents%20a%20pound%20no%20matter%20the%20item.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20arrived%20to%20a%20cabin%20in%20a%20state%20of%20disrepair%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20family%20and%20I%20drove%20down%20to%20the%20Poconos%20in%20a%20vintage%20camper%20that%20we%20bought%20in%202016.%20It%20was%20so%20late%20at%20night%20when%20we%20finally%20arrived%20in%20town%2C%20but%20we%20wanted%20to%20see%20the%20house%20right%20away.%20We%20had%20only%20seen%20photos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20got%20to%20the%20house%2C%20it%20was%20around%209%20p.m.%20and%20pitch%20dark.%20It%20did%20not%20have%20any%20power%2C%20so%20we%20had%20to%20use%20flashlights%20to%20get%20around.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20man%20that%20had%20lived%20in%20the%20home%20prior%20was%20a%20chain%20smoker%2C%20and%20we%20discovered%20yellow%20film%20on%20all%20the%20windows.%20He%20also%20had%20a%20wood-burning%20fireplace%20and%20the%20stove%20was%20not%20ventilating%20properly%2C%20so%20the%20carpet%20was%20stained%20and%20a%20different%20color%20in%20every%20room.%20It%20was%20horrific.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20just%20sort%20of%20laughed%20about%20it.%20We%20were%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20the%20heck%20can%20we%20do%3F%26quot%3B%C2%A0%20We%20were%20still%20excited%20about%20the%20potential%20of%20the%20home%20and%20knew%20we%20could%20make%20it%20nice.%20We%20embraced%20it%20as%20a%20part%20of%20the%20adventure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223621%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Danielle's%20husband%20working%20with%20an%20electrical%20saw.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65257bce55f52b01b35b250c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222721%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKyle%20Elderkin%20working%20with%20an%20electrical%20saw.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Niv%20Rosenberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20not%20in%20condition%20for%20us%20to%20move%20in%20right%20away%20and%20live%20in.%20It%20needed%20to%20be%20cleaned%20a%20lot%2C%20and%20the%20carpet%20had%20to%20be%20torn%20up.%20So%20we%20stayed%20with%20my%20sister%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20weeks%2C%20while%20my%20husband%20did%20some%20initial%20demo%20work.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20our%20first%20date%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20have%20always%20talked%20about%20wanting%20to%20renovate%20houses.%20We%20knew%20we%20were%20going%20to%20update%20this%20cabin%20and%20incorporate%20all%20things%20that%20we%20really%20love.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20made%20the%20kitchen%20bigger%20and%20included%20more%20cabinets.%20We%20kept%20the%20bedrooms%20pretty%20much%20the%20same%20and%20painted%20the%20paneling%20and%20brightened%20the%20rooms%20up.%20We%20renovated%20two%20bathrooms%2C%20which%20were%20really%20fun%20to%20do.%20We%20installed%20a%20vintage%20clawfoot%20tub%20and%20fun%20tile.%C2%A0It%20took%20us%20about%20three%20and%20a%20half%20years%20to%20renovate%20the%20cabin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20that%20time%20my%20husband%20had%20a%20full-time%20job%20working%20in%20construction%20at%20a%20local%20resort%2C%20and%20was%20renovating%20the%20cabin%20on%20the%20side.%20During%20that%20time%2C%20we%20also%20bought%20a%20second%20cabin%2C%20renovated%20it%20completely%2C%20and%20sold%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202022%2C%20we%20moved%20from%20the%20first%20cabin%20into%20the%20third%20cabin%20we%20bought.%20For%20now%2C%20this%20is%20our%20house%2C%20at%20least%20until%20our%20boys%20graduate%20from%20high%20school.%20But%20we%20definitely%20are%20planning%20on%20acquiring%20more%20properties.%20Right%20now%2C%20we're%20looking%20at%20the%20short-term%20rental%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt%20took%20time%20to%20adjust%20to%20a%20smaller%20living%20space%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELiving%20in%20a%20smaller%20space%2C%20you%20have%20to%20get%20really%20creative%20with%20using%20every%20inch%20of%20the%20house%20in%20a%20useful%20way.%20You%20can't%20just%20throw%20things%20in%20a%20giant%20closet%2C%20because%20you%20don't%20have%20that.%20Everything%20is%20super%20organized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20the%20boys%20hated%20sharing%20a%20room.%20They're%2019%20months%20apart%20and%20territorial%20and%20competitive.%20As%20they%20got%20older%2C%20they%20just%20really%20wanted%20their%20own%20space.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224535%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20cabin%20that%20was%20purchaed%20by%20the%20Elderkin's.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65257c1a68f1d46f52ad4588%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223401%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20cabin%20that%20was%20purchased%20by%20the%20Elderkins.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Niv%20Rosenberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20actually%20loved%20downsizing.%20Being%20trapped%20in%20our%20house%20during%20the%20shutdown%2C%20we%20really%20made%20the%20most%20of%20it.%20Looking%20back%2C%20those%20were%20some%20of%20the%20best%20times%20that%20we've%20all%20had%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20played%20a%20lot%20of%20board%20games%2C%20watched%20movies%2C%20and%20took%20cooking%20classes%20online.%20We%20were%20trying%20new%20things%20all%20the%20time.%20One%20of%20my%20sons%20learned%20to%20juggle%20and%20the%20other%20did%20magic.%20It%20was%20just%20really%20good%20bonding%20time%20for%20us%20all.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe're%20spending%20more%20time%20together%20as%20a%20family%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20so%20different%20living%20in%20the%20Poconos.%20Though%20we're%20still%20living%20pretty%20simply%2C%20money%20isn't%20so%20much%20a%20focus%20for%20us%20anymore.%20When%20we%20sold%20our%20first%20cabin%2C%20we%20went%20to%20Disney%20World.%20If%20we%20were%20still%20living%20in%20California%2C%20we%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20able%20to%20afford%20that%20vacation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20sister%20lives%20close%20by%2C%20so%20my%20sons%20have%20their%20cousins%20who%20are%20close%20in%20age%20to%20them.%20But%20because%20we%20moved%20towards%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20for%20a%20while%2C%20they%20didn't%20have%20any%20interaction%20with%20anyone%20except%20Zoom.%20It%20was%20challenging%20because%20the%20boys%20missed%20their%20friends.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223263%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Elderkins.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65257f0168f1d46f52ad4dbb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222451%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDanielle%20Elderkin%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20Kyle.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Niv%20Rosenberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20they%20went%20back%20to%20school%2C%20they%20really%20got%20to%20know%20people.%20They're%20now%20in%20sports%2C%20band%2C%20and%20drama.%20My%20older%20son%20is%20in%20a%20bunch%20of%20AP%20and%20honors%20classes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20family%20definitely%20spends%20more%20time%20together%2C%20especially%20living%20in%20a%20smaller%20space.%20But%20I%20do%20miss%20my%20family%20that%20still%20lives%20in%20California.%20Even%20still%2C%20I%20think%20we%20are%20probably%20going%20to%20stay%20in%20this%20area%20and%20keep%20it%20as%20our%20home%20base.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dream%20was%20for%20us%20to%20have%20more%20time%20together%20as%20a%20family%2C%20and%20to%20focus%20on%20renovating%20houses.%20I%20think%20the%20timing%20of%20everything%20worked%20out%20perfectly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-we-downsized-california-poconos-tiny-cabin-better-life-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697016601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6525be7268f1d46f52adcbbc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-we-downsized-california-poconos-tiny-cabin-better-life-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Elderkins%20were%20tired%20of%20California%20and%20downsized%20to%20Pennsylvania.%20The%20move%20was%20a%20disaster%20and%20the%20cabin%20was%20in%20disrepair.%20%26quot%3BWe%20embraced%20it.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22alloyd%40insider.com%20(Alcynna%20Lloyd)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-we-downsized-california-poconos-tiny-cabin-better-life-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Last%20Pieces%20Of%20Titanic%20Submersible%20Recovered%20By%20US%20Coast%20Guard%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EHuman%20remains%20and%20remnants%20from%20the%20Titan%20submersible%2C%20which%20tragically%20exploded%20while%20en%20route%20to%20explore%20the%20Titanic%20wreck%20in%20the%20Atlantic%20Ocean%2C%20have%20been%20retrieved%20b