MI.%20The%20police%20claimed%20that%20the%20visit%20was%20part%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Croutine%20check%E2%80%9D%20on%20people%20who%20were%20involved%20in%20terror%20cases.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20could%20have%20sent%20me%20a%20notice%20and%20asked%20me%20to%20come%20to%20the%20police%20station.%20I%20would%20have%20done%20that.%20But%20coming%20to%20my%20house%20and%20interrogating%20me%20in%20front%20of%20my%20family%2C%20even%20when%20there%20is%20no%20complaint%20against%20me%2C%20is%20an%20attempt%20to%20threaten%20me%E2%80%A6%20The%20court%20found%20all%20charges%20against%20me%20to%20be%20untrue.%20I%20am%20like%20any%20other%20normal%20Indian%20citizen.%20Do%20policemen%20walk%20into%20the%20houses%20of%20normal%20individuals%20and%20interrogate%20them%20in%20front%20of%20their%20families%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20Mumbai%20police%20commissioner.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThough%20not%20a%20practising%20lawyer%2C%20Wahid%20gives%20advice%20to%20people%20who%20he%20thinks%20are%20in%20the%20same%20position%20as%20he%20was%20%E2%80%93%20falsely%20accused%20in%20a%20case.%20In%20affidavits%20seeking%20custody%20of%20some%20PFI%20members%2C%20the%20police%20mentioned%20that%20they%20were%20in%20touch%20with%20Abdul%20Wahid.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20case%2C%20the%20Delhi%20police%20mentioned%20his%20name%20and%20claimed%20that%20he%20is%20a%20terrorist%20sympathiser%20who%20travels%20around%20the%20country%20under%20the%20garb%20of%20activism%20for%20prisoners%E2%80%99%20rights%20but%20is%20actually%20raising%20funds%20for%20terror%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20fear%20that%20such%20claims%20may%20be%20used%20to%20implicate%20me%20in%20a%20false%20case%20again%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0after%20all%2C%20it%20has%20happened%20to%20other%20people%20before%2C%E2%80%9D%20Wahid%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20defence%20will%20be%20stronger%20this%20time%2C%20but%20I%20also%20know%20that%20provisions%20that%20allow%20th